<title>USA: Health Systems Foundation Health.</title>
<headline>Health Systems Foundation Health.</headline>
<dateline>PUEBLO, Colorado 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foundation Health Systems Inc and Health Systems International Inc said Tuesday they completed their merger and that shares of the new company will begin trading Tuesday under the symbol FHS on the New York Stock Exchange.</p>
<p>The merger creates the fourth largest publicly-traded managed care company in the U.S., with close to five million members in 17 states. Pro forma revenues were about $7.1 billion in 1996, the companies said.</p>
<p>Under the terms of the merger, Foundation shareholders received 1.3 shares of FHS stock for each Foundation share they held.</p>
